sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K531010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Constitutive promoter and RBS BBa_K081005 + Caulobacter optimized dspB + rsaA C
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Constitutive promoter and RBS from the Registry BBa_K081005, suspected N-acetylglucosaminidase dspB codon optimized for Caulobacter, and the C-terminal secretion tag from Caulobacter's S-layer associated protein, RsaA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Alexander Aaring
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: BBa_K081005 was designed by Lorenzo Pasotti and Paolo Magni from Team UNIPV-Pavia 2008. IDT synthesized dspB so as to codon optimize it for expression in Caulobacter crescentus. The C-terminal secretion tag from rsaA is from the genome of the Caulobacter lab strain CB15N.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Stop codon at the end of dspB was removed to ensure expression of the rsaA C-terminal secretion tag.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K531004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: dspB from Actinobacillus actinomycetemcomitansis optimized for Caulobacter crescentus
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: DspB comes from the bacteria Actinobacillus actinomycetemcomitansis. It is most likely an N-acetylglucosaminidase that causes the detachment of cells from biofilm colonies through the 1→ 4 glycosidic bond of β-substituted N-acetylglucosamine. DspB is homologous to family 20 glycosyl hydrolases which cleave terminal monosaccharide residues.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nora Kostow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Kaplan, J., Ragunath, C., Ramasubbu, N., and Fine, D. Detachment of Actinobacillus actinomycetemcomitans Biofilm Cells by an Endogenous beta-Hexosaminidase Activity. Journal of Bacteriology. 2003 August; 185(16): 4693-4698.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The WT gene has a low GC content ~40%. Caulobacter crescentus is GC rich and prefers a high GC content. Therefore, we optimized the GC content by comparing the codons in the wild type dspB gene to their corresponding amino acid codons that are most expressed in Caulobacter. We also eliminated the stop codon at the end of dspB because we wanted to add another gene to it that also needed to be transcribed.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K531001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a secretion tag for secretion via a Type I secretion pathway in ''Caulobacter crescentus''. It should be appended to the C-terminal end of another protein to act as a secretion tag.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Alexander Aaring
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Using the Registry's suggested primer combinations results in the formation of an in sequence stop codon between two coding regions. A one nucleotide change was necessary in both the prefix of this coding sequence and the suffix of the coding region to be added in front of this gene to ensure that their is no stop codon in sequence.
